# Solvio brand

## Canonical assets — `public/brand/`

- `icon-source.png` — 1024×1024 master square icon (purple gradient rounded square, white stylized "S" with two circuit-node dots). Treat as the brand source of truth.
- `icon-512.png`, `icon-192.png`, `icon-96.png` — pre-resized square icons for manifest / in-app use.
- `wordmark-source.png` — 1024×1024 master with icon + "Solvio" wordmark.

## Next.js metadata files — `src/app/`

These are auto-discovered by Next.js App Router. Do not rename them.

- `icon.png` (512) — favicon / `/icon`
- `apple-icon.png` (180) — iOS home-screen
- `opengraph-image.png` (1200×630) — social cards
- `twitter-image.png` (1200×630) — duplicate of OG for `twitter:image`

## Rules

1. **Header / footer / sidebar logo mark** = `<Image src="/brand/icon-192.png" />` inside a `h-9 w-9 rounded-xl overflow-hidden` wrapper. Never re-implement the mark as a CSS gradient with a hand-rolled "S" character — that was the old placeholder.
2. **Wordmark text** = `<SolvioWordmark />` from `@/components/brand/solvio-wordmark` (animated clip-path reveal). The image wordmark in `public/brand/wordmark-source.png` is for OG / external use, not for in-page rendering — the React text wordmark scales better and is accessible.
3. **Primary brand color** = `#7c3aed` (violet-600). Gradient extension `from-[#7c3aed] to-[#a78bfa]` is fine for accents but is no longer the logo mark itself.
4. **Theme color** for browser chrome / PWA = `#7c3aed` — already set via `viewport.themeColor` in `src/app/layout.tsx`.
5. **Regenerating sizes**: source images are 1024×1024. Use `sips -Z <max> source.png --out dest.png` on macOS, or `sharp` in Node. Always start from `icon-source.png` / `wordmark-source.png`, never re-resize an already-shrunk file.
6. **Do not commit external/customer logos to `public/brand/`** — that folder is exclusively Solvio's own identity. Merchant logos belong in Supabase storage or under `public/customers/` if shipped statically.

## When the user provides new brand artwork

Replace `icon-source.png` / `wordmark-source.png` first, then regenerate every derived size with `sips` (or `sharp`). Re-deploy to production — favicons and OG images are CDN-cached so a fresh deploy + browser cache bust may be needed to see changes.
